Job Highlights

Website and mobile app user interface designs
Graphic and digital design for banner
Work with project and development team

Job Responsibilities

Website and mobile app user interface designs;
Produce all kind of graphic and digital design for banner and other presentation materials;
Work with project and development team; and
Manage any ad-hoc tasks or projects as assigned.

Job Requirements:

Higher Diploma or above in digital design, multimedia design, graphic communications or related field;
Minimum 1 years' of working experience in design related field
Hands on skills in Adobe Photoshop, Illustrator, Sketch;
Knowledge of UI design principles and techniques;
Detail minded with can-do attitude and ability to multitask;
Provide online portfolio link in addition to resume. *Immediate availability is preferred

Working location & hours

5-days work
Work in Kwun Tong

Duties:

Serve a contract assignment under InfoTech's headcount, full-time second to a statutory body;
Run a small development team to deliver customer-facing websites or applications;
Work closely with business and IT teams to manage and deliver web projects;
Customize and enhance the Council's CMS solution, TeamSite and WordPress;
Manage external vendors to fulfil integration requirements when necessary;
Participate in IT project activities, such as system design, feasibility study, effort estimation and scheduling.
Requirements:

5 years' or above experience in web development, including 2 years' or more experience in leading a development team; candidate with less experience may be considered as Senior Analyst Programmer;
Higher Diploma or above in Computer Science, IT or a related discipline preferred;
Strong in front-end development such as HTML5, CSS3 and JavaScript; knowledge and experience in RWD (Responsive Web Design), SPA (Single-page Application), e.g. ReactJS is a must;
Knowledge and experience in back-end development technology stack, e.g. Windows, Linux, Apache, NginX, MariaDB and Node.js;
Experience in cloud such as AWS and CMS such as TeamSite and WordPress is a bonus;
Knowledge of project management methodology. Holder of PMP, Agile, Scrum or equivalent qualifications is an advantage;
Ability to work independently or with a team to meet tight project deadlines.
Original JD      Direct: 3978 8032

Job Highlights 

Digital Media (DL.theVOC) + Technical Creative Projects + UI / UX Design

Good sense of art direction, graphic sense

Working with Award winning Creatives

Job Description: 

Provide full creative, design, project art direction and production support;

Responsible for social media OG design, GDN banner, graphics design, video editing, animation and other marketing materials;

Creating different designs for marketing use purpose in different platform such as desktop, mobile as well as kiosk;

Knowledge & experience in digital media industry is a plus; 

Requirements:

Diploma or above in Graphic / Multimedia / Web design or related fields;

Minimum 2 years’ relevant experience in graphic design, web design or advertising;

Photography and photo retouching, video post production, sound editing skills

Proficient in using PC / Mac Systems, Adobe Creative Cloud specifically Photoshop, Illustrator, Premiere, After Effects and other essential multimedia, interactive softwares, WordPress, Microsoft Office and other relevant software applications, familiar with HTML / HTML5 / CSS / JS is a plus;

Working knowledge of SEO best practice, GDN Display Ads, familiar with UI / UX design (Adobe XD, Figma, Sketch) is a big plus;

Strong multimedia and web sense and understanding of digital technology trends;

Creative, detail-oriented, enthusiastic, independent and self-motivated;

Good written and spoken in English and Chinese;

A perfect team player;

Portfolio attachment is a MUST;

Candidates with less experience would also be considered as Associate Art Director;

 Benefits:

Annual Leave

Birthday Leave

Performance Bonus

Medical Insurance

We offer 5–day work week, competitive salary and fringe benefits to the right candidate. For interested parties please send a cover letter stating your current salary and expected salary with Resume, Graduation Certification and Transcript to us.

Candidates who are not contacted within 1 month from sending the resume should consider your applications filed for future opportunities. All applications will be treated in strict confidentiality and used for recruitment purpose only

